[74.144239, "o", " branch\\n\\nNow I'm designing the test structure for a maze-based scenario.\\n\\nFor the no-path and start==end cases, I'll pull from PathTestScenarios but generate fresh grids for isolation. For the `_jump` test on `JPFNeverMoveDiagonally`, I need to call it directly with matching coordinates so dx and dy both equal zero, which requires setting up the finder's grid and endNode. For the forced-neighbor diagonal test in `JPFMoveDiagonallyIfAtMostOneObstacle`, I need a layout where one adjacent cell is blocked but the diagonal is walkable, and I'll handle the blocked diagonal case similarly.\\n\\nNow I'm thinking through the test structure—I need to verify the early-return null condition where both orthogonal neighbors are blocked, handle the closed jump point case in `_identifySuccessors`, and check the openList update branch. I should also verify instanceof checks for the factory test and use the existing mocha/should pattern from PathTest.js.\\n\\nWriting the test file... Let me trace through this more carefully."]
